Executive Summary

A simulated brute-force SSH attack was conducted against an Ubuntu system. Log analysis identified repeated failed login attempts from a single IP address. The incident was classified as a credential brute-force attempt.

Immediate containment and remediation actions were taken to secure the system.

Root Cause Analysis

The server allowed password-based authentication, enabling repeated login attempts.

Impact Assessment

No successful unauthorized access

Increased risk exposure

Potential credential compromise risk

Remediation Implemented

Enabled SSH key authentication

Disabled password authentication

Configured firewall rules

Preventive Recommendations

Implement Fail2Ban

Enable account lockout policy

Use intrusion detection systems

Conduct regular log monitoring
